arch:property.oc:show_val: Fairly big unit, quite even body part distribution, mostly sheep-size with some large mammal, some burning, most of that low temperature, some digestion, a little bit of gnawing, weathering variable, but mostly very well preserved, quite fragmented, probably waste from daily household consumption. Sample 2 >4mm flotation sorted 100%, only diagnostics recorded completely, rest as flot frags. Largish sample, mostly sheep-size crumbles, some large mammal. Some burning, mostly low temperature. Some digestion, quite a bit of gnawing. Weathering variable, mostly fairly good condition. Two fish vertebrae. Last number =256

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
